# Awesome PG — Live AI brain (MEMORY engine)

Vault: `/Users/aashumotlani/awesomepg/docs` · Rules: `docs/.cursor/rules.md`

## Classify before writing

| Type | File |
|------|------|
| Live focus, blockers, priorities | `docs/MEMORY/active_memory.md` |
| Actionable work | `docs/MEMORY/tasks.md` |
| Strategic idea | `docs/MEMORY/ideas.md` |
| Decision made | `docs/MEMORY/decisions.md` |
| Insight / lesson | `docs/MEMORY/insights.md` |
| Bug / problem | `docs/MEMORY/bugs.md` |
| Mistake / failure | `docs/MEMORY/mistakes.md` |
| Vault update | `docs/MEMORY/changelog.md` |

Formal registries: `docs/BUGS.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/DECISIONS.md` — cross-link from MEMORY.

## After meaningful vault edits

1. Append to the correct MEMORY file (never delete history)
2. Update `active_memory.md` if focus, blockers, or priorities changed
3. Append one line to `MEMORY/changelog.md`
4. Run: `cd docs && ./scripts/brain-sync.sh`

## Do not

- Dump unstructured notes into SYSTEM/ or PROJECT/
- Overwrite or delete MEMORY history
- Force-push the vault repo
